Spanish and Italian? By the use of what lexical, syntactic and grammatical devices? Will the learner combine these devices as the native French speakers do? What are the L1 features likely to fossilize in the L2 grammar? What are the information principles governing a communicative task based on the production of counterfactual scenarios? These are some of the questions addressed by the present volume.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCounterfactuals (Logic) 0aCounterfactuals (Logic). 0aDecision making. 0aFrench languagexGrammar. 0aFrench languagexSemantics. 0aFrench languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aItalian languagexGrammar. 0aItalian languagexSemantics. 0aLanguage and logic. 0aSecond language acquisition. 0aSpanish languagexGrammar. 0aSpanish languagexSemantics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aCounterfactuality.  aDecision-Making.  aIrrealis.  aSecond Language Acquisition.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2018 Part 1z978311076248808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Contemporary 2016-2019z978311074297808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018 Englishz978311060407808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018z9783110603170oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015077240 cprintz978150151613940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150150778640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501507786423